node.text:
#AmbersCountryKitchen! Here's my recipe 🎬 for the #RoyalBreadBakeOff 🍞I've called my creation "Jersey Milk🐮& Honey🐝 Bread". I've included the step-by-step directions so you can give it a try yourselves, because it truly tastes pretty sweet - if I do say so myself! 
Thanks to The Royal Agricultural Winter Fair for creating such a fun contest!

I had so much fun making this recipe and the bread was SO good my husband and I ate it all in one day…. So… maybe it was a little too good. The bread was made with whole milk from my Jersey cow and I served it with warm local honey and homemade butter - made of course from my Jersey cream! 
Ingredients 
2 packets of active dry yeast (approx. 2¼ teaspoons)
2.5 cups of warm whole milk (Heated to 110F)
1/3 cup of honey
¼ cup of melted butter
2 teaspoons of salt
7-8 cups of all-purpose flour
Olive oil
Sunflower & Sesame seeds

What you need
Double Boiler
Mixing bowl with cover
Whisk & Spatula
Baking dishes (x2)
Food thermometer
Oven mitts
Wire cooling rack 
STEP ONE: Warm your whole milk in a double boiler until it reaches 110-115F. Pour warm milk in a large bowl (or stand mixer) and add yeast. Whisk together until yeast is fully dissolved. Mix in honey, butter and salt. Add 5 cups of flour and once well combined add remaining flour (or as much as you need to form a nice soft dough). STEP TWO: Knead your dough on a floured board until it is smooth and elastic (which takes around 6-8 minutes). Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease both sides. Cover and let rise in a warm area until doubled (about an hour). STEP THREE: Punch your dough back down and break into two loaves. Place loves in greased loaf pans. Cover and let ride again (about 30 minutes). STEP FOUR: Cover loaves with a drizzle of honey, sunflower and sesame seeds. Place in pre-heated oven at 350F and bake for 30-35 min (until golden brown) 
STEP FIVE:
Remove from loaf pans and let cool on a wire rack. Slice and serve!

Just because you are stuck at home doesn’t mean you can’t spend time with your friends! It just means you have to get creative on how you “hang out!” I love that Michelle and I can enjoy a good old throwback while watching my favourite Heartland Season 6 episode!! ❤️
.
.
What is your favourite Heartland episode in Season 6? Tell us which one and why, and we will enter your name in a draw to WIN a signed Season 6 DVD set!!!! 🥰
.
.

node.text:
Smiling contently like these two tonight! 😊

Had a beautiful and quiet long weekend on the farm. Decided this was my time to tackle my “To-Do List!” I made no plans, just worked steady and I’m feeling pretty accomplished right now! ✅✅

If you missed my recent post about my new pup… then please meet Rein. She is a 2 year old Border Collie who snuck her way into my heart. 😋

Hope everyone had a restful, productive or just all around enjoyable weekend. I’m now ready to tackle this short (but very busy) work week!

#AmbersDogRemi
#AmbersDogRein #PuppySmiles #DogLife #FarmDogs #HappyDogs

node.text: A few days ago I was asked about the bird variety at my new home. Since we moved from very open land to heavily treed I am constantly in awe by the variety of birds here. This weekend I managed to capture this little guy feeding on bugs in an old stump. These Pileated Woodpeckers are among my favourite birds to watch. 🌲#PileatedWoodpecker

node.text:
It was an incredible experience working with Dan and his team. I can’t wait for you all to see what we were up to in the opening episode of season 15!! 🎬

Re-Posted from•@doubledanhorsemanship 

“At long last...we've been waiting to share this for months!

"Double Dan Horsemanship recently had the privilege to work on one of the most wholesome family favorite horse TV shows in the world (literally) - Heartland for the start of their 15th Season. We cannot thank the Heartland team and Amber Marshall enough for this incredible experience. Amber (Amy) was for all of you Heartland fans out there just as down to earth and sincere as the character.  It was really refreshing to meet someone with as much success and fame that still has so much humility and kindness. I personally couldn't have been more proud of my horses in the way they performed and how they did their jobs so incredibly and professionally. Thank you to my wife (and our team) who kept the wheels of life and business on track throughout the process. Above all...thank God for the horse!"
- Dan James

Dan will be sharing the behind the scenes stories and exclusive footage that won't be shared anywhere else on a Zoom Call with all of the DDH Insiders next week. You don't want to miss it!

Already an Insider? Check your email today for details and to submit your questions. 

Not a DDH Insider yet? Join today by checking out our website in the bio (your first month is free and you can cancel at any time).”

#LibertyHorses
#DoubleDanHorsemanship
#HLinProd
